         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">12/3/87 ¶  ¶ I don't know whether I've already told you, dear Mr Holtze, that I have to work on a few Verbenaceae in context. In order to do that, I would like to have ripe fruit specimens of your No....</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">87.03.12</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Maurice Holtze</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">GRG 19/391, State Records of South Australia, Adelaide.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">12/3/87</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich weiss nicht, ob ich Ihnen schon geschrieben, lieber Herr Holtze, dass ich einige Verbenaceen im Zusammenhang zu bearbeiten habe, u. dafür auch gerne reife Frucht-Exemplare Ihrer 644 haben möchte. Ist die Blume weiss? Sollte irgend ein Bekannter Gelegenheit haben die Adansonia Region zu besuchen, würden Sie ihn bitte eine Anzahl Blüthen in Papier zu pressen und nahe einem Feuer zu trocknen. Die Blumen und auch Blätter sind für die Museen der meisten botanisch Gärten noch neu. Ich möchte Ihnen gern Allerlei senden, weiss aber nicht, was Sie von hier brauchen. </seg>Bestens grüssend der Ihre</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">12/3/87</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I don't know whether I've already told you, dear Mr Holtze, that I have to work on a few <name key="Verbenaceae">Verbenaceae</name> in context. In order to do that, I would like to have ripe fruit specimens of your No. 644. Is the flower white?<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to M. Holtze, <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">
                        <hi rend="underline">list 1887</hi>
                     </seg>. <seg style="background-color: #ffff00; ">M later determined the specimen to be a new species which he named </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; background-color: #ffff00; ">Clerodendron holtzei</seg>
                     <seg style="background-color: #ffff00; "> (B91.05.07); however, no Holtze specimen numbered 644 now appears in the AVH lists (accessed 17 March 2022).</seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="color: #c00000; ">This seems a poor <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>attribution argument, even though it may be correct. Clerodendron = Clerodendrum is a Lamiaceae, not <name key="Verbenaceae">Verbenaceae</name> However many that were in Verbebaceae are now in Lamiacea</seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="color: #c00000; ">The specimen treated as the type MEL 98246 has Holtze number 995, see </seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="color: #c00000; ">90-05-16-final.doc,</seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; color: #c00000; "
                     xml:lang="en">90-06-26-final.doc</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; color: #c00000; "
                     xml:lang="en">90-06-00a-final.doc</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="color: #c00000; ">See also description at </seg>
                     <ref target="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/41898099#page/131/"
                          rend="Internet%20link"
                          style="color: #0563c1; ">
                        <seg rend="Internet%20link" style="color: #0563c1; ">B91.05.07</seg>
                     </ref>
                  </p>
               </note> Should any acquaintance of yours have the opportunity to visit the Adansonia region, would you please ask him to press a number of flowers in paper and dry them close to a fire. The flowers and also the leaves are for the museums of most botanical gardens still new. I would like to send you a few things, but I don't know what you might need from here.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Best wishes</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Verbenaceae">Verbenaceae</name>
            </p>
         </div>
